{"title":"Irving Penn: Small Trades","link":"https://kottke.org/24/09/irving-penn-small-trades","date":1726089516000,"content":"\n        <p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/irving-penn-small-trades-01.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/irving-penn-small-trades-01.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/irving-penn-small-trades-01.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1775\" alt=\"black &amp; white photo of two bakers\" /></p>\n\n<p>In 1950, master photographer Irving Penn set up a simple studio in Paris and started to photograph people of all kinds of professions, each wearing their work clothes and carrying the tools of their trade.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/irving-penn-small-trades-02.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/irving-penn-small-trades-02.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/irving-penn-small-trades-02.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1627\" alt=\"black &amp; white photo of a man selling chestnuts from a cart\" /></p>\n\n<p>Working in the <a href=\"https://www.meisterdrucke.uk/fine-art-prints/French-School/1068212/Les-Petits-Metiers-de-Paris,-Image-of-Epinal-of-the-19th-Century.html\">tradition</a> of representing the <a href=\"https://histoire-image.org/etudes/petits-metiers-paris-albums-eugene-atget\">petits mÃ©tiers</a>, Penn photographed fishmongers, firefighters, butchers, bakers, divers, baseball umpires, chefs, bike messengers, and sellers of goods of all kinds.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/irving-penn-small-trades-03.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/irving-penn-small-trades-03.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/irving-penn-small-trades-03.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1744\" alt=\"black &amp; white photo of a deep sea diver posing\" /></p>\n\n<p>Penn continued photographing workers in New York and London, collecting the photos into a project called <a href=\"https://irvingpenn.org/small-trades\">Small Trades</a>.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/irving-penn-small-trades-04.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/irving-penn-small-trades-04.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/irving-penn-small-trades-04.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1421\" alt=\"black &amp; white photo of two tradewomen carrying buckets\" /></p>\n\n<p>Penn <a href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=dB6QKdnGeioC&amp;lpg=PA1&amp;pg=PA14#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\">said of the project</a>:</p>\n\n<blockquote><p>Like everyone else who has recorded the look of tradesmen and workers, the author of this book was motivated by the fact that individuality and occupational pride seem on the wane. To a degree everyone has proved right, and since these photographs were made, London chimney sweeps have all but disappeared and in New York horseshoers â€” hard to find in 1950 â€” now scarcely exist.</p></blockquote>\n\n<p>A possible companion to Pennâ€™s photographs: Studs Terkelâ€™s <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1565843428/ref=nosim/0sil8\">Working: People Talk About What They Do All Day and How They Feel About What They Do</a>. (Fun fact: Terkel and his editor <a href=\"https://austinkleon.com/2018/05/11/what-do-people-do-all-day/\">got the idea for Working</a> from Richard Scarryâ€™s childrenâ€™s book, <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0553520598/ref=nosim/0sil8\">What Do People Do All Day?</a>)</p>\n\n        \n\n         <p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/art\">art</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/books\">books</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/Irving%20Penn\">Irving Penn</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/photography\">photography</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/Studs%20Terkel\">Studs Terkel</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/working\">working</a></p>\n\n         <p>ðŸ’¬ <a href=\"https://kottke.org/24/09/irving-penn-small-trades\">Join the discussion on kottke.org</a> â†’</p>\n\n    ","author":"Jason Kottke","siteTitle":"Kottke","siteHash":"89a883271b4598f9b33ebe87be70d38557bcd266e68aee521a8f93622e0ab723","entryHash":"27fe59aa16075f131e4dada7f171f565a5125c80c9e65228f4970f699488422d","category":"Sites"}